  ),
)


Here's what these patterns look like on the page.


The strongest romantic technology constraints produce what you might call #emph[micro-intimacy with interruption]: touch that must be hidden, words that must be delayed, care that must be given without claiming ownership. The interruption keeps the barrier intact while still feeding the relationship, which is why stolen moments under surveillance land harder than leisurely conversations in safety. If you can only touch for three seconds before someone rounds the corner, those three seconds carry the weight of an entire scene.


